<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-064-658  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 064 658.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Feb 20 1989 v11 n8 p68(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Automator. (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Black, Lauren L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Direct Technology's Automator is a software application that willautomate or customize any PC process.andP;  It contains a universalscripting language that facilitates technical programming withoutany programming knowledge.andP;  Hot keys or macros can be created thatwill make PC operations simple for the less experienced user.andP;  Thelearn mode provides a program generator, editor, interpreter, andcompiler.andP;  Automator can be set up as event-sensitive andinstructed to watch for four specific types of events: keyboardentries, system clock events, on-screen events, and a specialWhen-user command.andP;  Automator increases productivity and makes useof previously wasted computer time by performing software tests ordownloading during the night or other times when the system is notnormally in use.andP;  The $1,995 list price is expensive but thisprogram is a benefit to medium- to large-size companies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Direct Technology Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Automator (Computer program).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSoftware PackagesUtility ProgramsCustomization.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>